ntity that became Jersey City.His personal passion was to help promulgate the Christian message, especially through the founding of the American Bible Society and the New York Sunday School Union. A highly respected, multitalented businessman and national hero, he was returned to Hackensack for burial in 1831.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aMayorszNew York (State)zNew YorkvBiography. 0aRevolutionarieszNew York (State)vBiography. 0aRevolutionarieszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aSoldierszNew York (State)vBiography. 0aSoldierszUnited StatesvBiography. 4aGeneral Interest : Biography. 4aHistory : American History. 4aNew York/Regional : New York/Regional. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Historical.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143843986040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438439860423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438439860/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles